Time Model Statistics

  • DB Time represents total time in user calls
  • DB CPU represents CPU time of foreground processes
  • Total CPU Time represents foreground and background processes
  • Statistics including the word "background" measure background process time, therefore do not contribute to the DB time statistic
  • Ordered by % of DB time in descending order, followed by Statistic Name

sum(case when stat_type='reqs' and stat_name in ('fcoior', 'fckpior', 'fcoiorqrm', 'fckpiorqrm', 'rcior', 'rciorm', 'pcior', 'pciorm', 'fciorrh') then total_value when stat_type = 'bytes' and stat_name in ('fcsiobyra', 'fcciobyelig') then total_value when stat_type = 'space' and stat_name in ('rcby', 'pcby') then current_value end) eff_denom, -- start column for additional information for fcc sum(case when stat_type= 'bytes' and stat_name = 'fcciobysave' then total_value end) fcciobysave, -- start columns for category reqs/bytes sum(case when stat_type = 'reqs' and in_cat_sum = 'Y' then total_value end) cat_rq, sum(case when stat_type = 'bytes' and in_cat_sum = 'Y' then total_value end) cat_by, sum(case when stat_type = 'reqs' and in_cat_sum = 'Y' then persec_value end) cat_rqps, sum(case when stat_type = 'bytes' and in_cat_sum = 'Y' then persec_value end) cat_byps, sum(case when stat_type = 'space' and in_cat_sum = 'Y' then current_value end) cat_spc from (-- calculate deltas select e.dbid, e.cell_hash, e.metric_id, e.metric_value - nvl(b.metric_value, 0) total_value, -- per second value (e.metric_value - nvl(b.metric_value, 0))/ :duration persec_value, -- current value e.metric_value current_value, -- get stat_name st.stat_name, st.stat_type, st.stat_category, st.stat_subcategory, st.in_cat_sum from dba_hist_cell_global b, dba_hist_cell_global e, xmltable('/stats/stat' passing xmltype(:fc_metadata) columns id number path '@id', stat_name varchar2(32) path '@name', stat_type varchar2(10) path '@type', stat_category varchar2(32) path '@cat', stat_subcategory varchar2(32) path '@sub', in_cat_sum varchar2(1) path '@in_cat_sum') st where e.dbid = :dbid and b.snap_id (+) = :bid and e.snap_id = :eid and b.dbid (+) = e.dbid and b.cell_hash (+) = e.cell_hash and b.incarnation_num (+) = e.incarnation_num and b.metric_id (+) = e.metric_id and (e.metric_id between 180 and 218 or e.metric_id between 300 and 307 or e.metric_id between 314 and 319 or e.metric_id between 370 and 380 or e.metric_id between 390 and 397 or e.metric_id between 441 and 464 or e.metric_id between 470 and 480 or e.metric_id between 540 and 559 or e.metric_id between 580 and 591) and e.metric_id = st.id) group by dbid, cell_hash, stat_name)) s where cn.dbid = s.dbid and cn.cell_hash = s.cell_hash and cn.snap_id = :eid ) select xmlelement("statsgroup", xmlagg(cells_xml order by category)) from ( select category, xmlelement("cellstats", xmlattributes(max(disp_category) as "type"), xmlagg(all_xml order by rn), xmlagg(cell_xml order by rn)) cells_xml from (-- group by category, cellname select category, max(disp_category) as disp_category, rn, case -- get 'All' node when rn = 1 and (max(cat_rq_s) is not null or max(cat_mb_s) is not null or max(cat_spcmb_s) is not null) then xmlelement("cell", xmlattributes('All' as "name", max(num_cells) as "num_cells"), -- add category stat case when category = '01-fc_ureads' and (max(cat_rq_s) is not null or max(cat_mb_s) is not null) then xmlelement("stat", xmlattributes('fcior' as "name", round(max(cat_rq_s), 2) as "rq", round(max(cat_rqps_s), 2) as "rqps", round(max(cat_mb_s), 2) as "mb", round(max(cat_mbps_s), 2) as "mbps")) when category = '04-fc_iwrites' and (max(cat_rq_s) is not null or max(cat_mb_s) is not null) then xmlelement("stat", xmlattributes('fciowt' as "name", round(max(cat_rq_s), 2) as "rq ", round(max(cat_rqps_s), 2) as "rqps", round(max(cat_mb_s), 2) as "mb", round(max(cat_mbps_s), 2) as "mbps")) end, xmlagg(all_xml order by rn), xmlagg(all_sub_xml order by rn), -- add XML for partial writes case when category = '02-fc_uwrites' and (max(fciorqwp_s) is not null or max(fciombwp_s) is not null) then xmlelement("stat", xmlattributes('fciowp' as "name", round(max(fciorqwp_s), 2) as "rq", round(max(fciorqwp_ps_s), 2) as "rqps", round(max(fciombwp_s), 2) as "mb", round(max(fciombwp_ps_s), 2) as "mbps", -- calculate % of total round( 100*max(fciorqwp_s)/ decode( max(cat_rq_s), 0, null, max(cat_rq_s)), 2) as "rqpct", -- calculate % of total round( 100*max(fciombwp_s)/ decode( max(cat_mb_s), 0, null, max(cat_mb_s)), 2) as "mbpct")) end, -- add XML for total rejections case when category = '12-fc_lwrej' and max(tmp_rq_s) is not null then xmlelement("stat", xmlattributes('fclwrejtot' as "name", round(max(tmp_rq_s), 2) as "rq", round(max(tmp_rqps_s), 2) as "rqps")) end, -- add XML for pmem clean case when category = '17-pc_spc' and max(pcbyoc_s) is not null then xmlelement("stat", xmlattributes('pcbyoc' as "name", "rq", round(max(cat_rqps), 2) as "rqps", round(max(cat_mb), 2) as "mb", round(max(cat_mbps), 2) as "mbps")) when category = '04-fc_iwrites' and (max(cat_rq) is not null or max(cat_mb) is not null) cat_total_value, cat_psec_value, cat_curr_value, -- calculate % of total case when category = 'reqs' -- pct of total reqs then 100*(total_value/decode(total_reqs, 0, null, total_reqs)) when category = 'rqsz' -- pct of all req sizes then 100*(total_value/ decode(cat_total_value, 0, null, cat_total_value)) when category = 'numbuf' -- pct of buffers then 100*(curr_value/ decode(cat_curr_value, 0, null, cat_curr_value)) when category = 'maxbuf' then 100*(max_buffers/ decode(num_buffers, 0, null, num_buffers)) end pct, total_value_s, psec_value_s, curr_value_s, num_buffers_s, cat_total_value_s, cat_psec_value_s, cat_curr_value_s, -- calculate % of total for 'All' -- no need to calculate buffer usage for 'All' case when category = 'reqs' then 100*(total_value_s/ decode(total_reqs_s, 0, null, total_reqs_s)) when category = 'rqsz' then 100*(total_value_s/ decode(cat_total_value_s, 0, null, cat_total_value_s)) end pct_s, -- we get order of stat the same way each time row_number() over (partition by metric_id order by metric_id desc) rn_stat, -- get first occurrence of band size row_number() over (partition by band order by total_reqs desc, cell_name) rn_band, -- rank cells by total requests dense_rank() over (order by total_reqs desc, cell_name) rn, num_cells from sys.awr_pdb_cell_name cn, (select dbid, cell_hash, metric_id, metric_name, category, band, case when band = '512' then 0 else to_number(replace(band, 'K', '')) end band_ordno, total_value, psec_value, curr_value, -- total for 'All' for a specific stat sum(total_value) over (partition by metric_id) total_value_s, sum(psec_value) over (partition by metric_id) psec_value_s, sum(curr_value) over (partition by metric_id) curr_value_s, -- total reqs for each cell sum(total_reqs) over (partition by cell_hash) total_reqs, -- total reqs for 'All' sum(total_reqs) over () total_reqs_s, -- get sum per category (i.e. write/buffers/etc to -- compute pct) per cell sum(total_value) over (partition by cell_hash, category) cat_total_value, sum(psec_value) over (partition by cell_hash, category) cat_psec_value, sum(curr_value) over (partition by cell_hash, category) cat_curr_value, -- compute category sum for 'All' sum(total_value) over (partition by category) cat_total_value_s, sum(psec_value) over (partition by category) cat_psec_value_s, sum(curr_value) over (partition by category) cat_curr_value_s, -- get buffers per band size per cell sum(num_buffers) over (partition by cell_hash, band) num_buffers, sum(max_buffers) over (partition by cell_hash, band) max_buffers, -- get buffers per band size for e.metric_id, e.metric_name, -- extract band size -- note we have 512 and 512K, may need to handle this case when e.metric_name != 'PMEM log write requests' then substr(e.metric_name, instr(e.metric_name, '-') + 2) end band, case when e.metric_name = 'PMEM log write requests' then 'treqs' when e.metric_name like 'PMEM log write requests -%' then 'reqs' when e.metric_name like 'PMEM log request size -%' then 'rqsz' when e.metric_name like 'PMEM log num buffers -%' then 'numbuf' when e.metric_name like 'PMEM log max buffers in use -%' then 'maxbuf' else null end category, (e.metric_value - b.metric_value) total_value, (e.metric_value - b.metric_value)/:duration psec_value, e.metric_value curr_value, -- get total writes as a separate column - for report decode(e.metric_id, 600, e.metric_value - b.metric_value, 0) total_reqs, -- partial pivot to calculate %max case when e.metric_name like 'PMEM log num buffers -%' then e.metric_value end num_buffers, case when e.metric_name like 'PMEM log max buffers in use -%' then e.metric_value end max_buffers from dba_hist_cell_global b, dba_hist_cell_global e where e.dbid = :dbid and b.snap_id (+) = :bid and e.snap_id = :eid and e.dbid = b.dbid (+) and e.cell_hash = b.cell_hash (+) and e.incarnation_num = b.incarnation_num (+) and e.metric_id = b.metric_id (+) and (e.metric_id = 600 or e.metric_id between 620 and 667))) s where cn.dbid = s.dbid and cn.cell_hash = s.cell_hash and cn.snap_id = :eid ) select case when buf_xml is not null and reqs_xml is not null then xmlelement("statsgroup", xmlattributes('pmemlog_bands' as "type"), case when band_xml is not null then xmlelement("bands", band_xml) end, reqs_xml, buf_xml) end from ( select xmlagg(xmlagg(band_xml)) band_xml, xmlagg( case when category in ('reqs', 'rqsz') and max(cat_total_value_s) > 0 then xmlelement("cellstats", xmlattributes('pmemlog_' || category as "type"), xmlelement("cell", xmlattributes('All' as "name", max(num_cells) as "num_cells "), xmlelement("stat", xmlattributes( '0' as "size", max(cat_total_value_s) as "value", round(max(cat_psec_value_s), 2) as "psec")), xmlagg(all_xml order by rn)), xmlagg(cell_xml order by rn)) end) reqs_xml, xmlagg( case when category = 'maxbuf' then xmlelement("cellstats", xmlattributes('pmemlog_buffers' as "type"), xmlagg(cell_buf_xml order by cell_name)) end) buf_xml from ( select rn, cell_name, category, max(num_cells) num_cells, max(cat_total_value_s) cat_total_value_s, max(cat_psec_value_s) cat_psec_value_s, -- get bands, expected to come from the same cell xmlagg( case when rn_band = 1 and band is not null then xmlelement("band", xmlattributes(band as "size"), band) end order by band_ordno) band_xml, -- xml for 'All' xmlagg( case when rn_stat = 1 and category in ('reqs', 'rqsz') and total_value_s > 0 then xmlelement("stat", xmlattributes(band as "size", total_value_s as "value", round(psec_value_s, 2) as "psec", round(pct_s, 2) as "pct", case when num_buffers_s > 0 then 'Y' end as "conf")) end order by metric_id) all_xml, case when category in ('reqs', 'rqsz') and max(cat_total_value) > 0 then xmlelement("cell", xmlattributes(cell_name as "name", rn as "rank"), xmlelement("stat", xmlattributes('0' as "size", max(cat_total_value) as "value", round(max(cat_psec_value), 2) as "psec")), xmlagg( case when total_value > 0 then xmlelement("stat", xmlattributes( band as "size", total_value as "value", round(psec_value, 2) as "psec", round(pct, 2) as "pct", -- if band was configured case when num_buffers > 0 then 'Y' end as "conf")) end order by band_ordno)) end cell_xml, -- max(num_buffers): if any buffer is configured for cell case when category = 'maxbuf' and max(num_buffers) > 0 then xmlelement("cell", xmlattributes(cell_name as "name", rn as "rank"), xmlagg( case when curr_value > 0 and num_buffers > 0 then xmlelement("stat", xmlattributes(band as "size", max_buffers as "value", num_buffers as "total", round(pct, 2) as "pct", max_buffers || '/' || num_buffers || ' (' || round(pct, 2) || '%)' as "display")) end order by band_ordno)) end cell_buf_xml from cellstats group by category, cell_name, rn) group by category)

7mnt0udg7t3q1 with disk_names as ( select /*+ materialize */ dbid, snap_id, cell_hash, disk_id, disk_name, disk from dba_hist_cell_disk_name where dbid = :dbid and snap_id = :eid ), cell_type as ( select dbid, snap_id, cellhash cell_hash, case when upper(extractvalue(xmltype(confval), '//makeModel')) like '%X7%EXTREME_FLASH%' or upper(extractvalue(xmltype(confval), '//makeModel')) like '%X8%EXTREME_FLASH%' or upper(extractvalue(xmltype(confval), '//makeModel')) like '%X9%EXTREME_FLASH%' then 0.5 else 1 end max_factor_iops, case when upper(extractvalue(xmltype(confval), '//makeModel')) like '%X7%EXTREME_FLASH%' then 0.5 when upper(extractvalue(xmltype(confval), '//makeModel')) like '%X8%EXTREME_FLASH%' or upper(extractvalue(xmltype(confval), '//makeModel')) like '%X9%EXTREME_FLASH%' then 0.8 else 1 end max_factor_mbps from dba_hist_cell_config_detail where dbid = :dbid and snap_id = :eid and conftype = 'CELL' ), disk_stats AS ( -- determine if getting to max capacity select dbid, cell_name, disk_id, disk_name, disk_type, num_disks, -- iops d_iops_a, d_iops_pct, dt_iops_m, dt_iops_v, dt_iops_cv, dt_iops_l, dt_iops_h, iops_bid, max_iops, case when d_iops_a > max_iops then 'Y' end is_max_iops, -- also check total case when dt_iops_m > max_iops then 'Y' end is_max_disk_iops, -- mbps d_mbps_a, d_mbps_pct, dt_mbps_m, dt_mbps_v, dt_mbps_cv, dt_mbps_l, dt_mbps_h, mbps_bid, max_mbps, case when d_mbps_a > max_mbps then 'Y' end is_max_mbps, case when dt_mbps_m > max_mbps then 'Y' end is_max_disk_mbps, -- utilization d_du_a, dt_du_m, dt_du_v, dt_du_cv, dt_du_l, dt_du_h, du_bid, -- service time d_st_a, dt_st_m, dt_st_v, dt_st_cv, dt_st_l, dt_st_h, st_bid, -- wait time d_wt_a, dt_wt_m, dt_wt_v, dt_wt_cv, dt_wt_l, dt_wt_h, wt_bid, -- ranks iops_rank, mbps_rank, wt_rank, -- outlier case when abs(iops_bid) >= 3 or abs(mbps_bid) >= 3 or abs(du_bid) >= 3 or abs(st_bid) >= 3 or abs(wt_bid) >= 3 then 1 else 0 end is_outlier from ( -- compute buckets and get low/high range, compute cv select dbid, cell_name, disk_id, disk_name, disk disk_type, num_disks, max_iops, max_mbps, -- iops d_iops_a, d_iops_pct, dt_iops_m, dt_iops_v, -- calculate cv case when dt_iops_m > 100 then dt_iops_v/dt_iops_m else 0 end dt_iops_cv, greatest(dt_iops_m - 3*dt_iops_v, 0) dt_iops_l, dt_iops_m + 3*dt_iops_v dt_iops_h, -- compute bucket id, do not consider idle systems case when (round(dt_iops_m, 2) = 0 and round(dt_iops_v, 2) = 0 and round(d_iops_a, 2) < 1) or round(d_iops_a, 2) < 10 then 0 else decode(dt_iops_v, 0, 0, trunc( (d_iops_a - dt_iops_m) / dt_iops_v )) end iops_bid, -- mbps d_mbps_a, d_mbps_pct, dt_mbps_m, dt_mbps_v, -- calculate cv case when dt_mbps_m > 100 then dt_mbps_v/dt_mbps_m else 0 end dt_mbps_cv, greatest(dt_mbps_m - 3*dt_mbps_v, 0) dt_mbps_l, dt_mbps_m + 3*dt_mbps_v dt_mbps_h, case when (round(dt_mbps_m, 2) = 0 and round(dt_mbps_v, 2) = 0 and round(d_mbps_a, 2) < 1) or round(d_iops_a, 2) < 10 then 0 else decode(dt_mbps_v, 0, 0, trunc( (d_mbps_a - dt_mbps_m) / dt_mbps_v )) end mbps_bid, -- disk utilization d_du_a, dt_du_m, dt_du_v, case when dt_du_m > 5 then dt_du_v/dt_du_m else 0 end dt_du_cv, greatest(dt_du_m - 3*dt_du_v, 0) dt_du_l, dt_du_m + 3*dt_du_v dt_du_h, case when (round(dt_du_m, 2) = 0 and round(dt_du_v, 2) = 0 and round(d_du_a, 2) < 1) or round(d_iops_a, 2) < 10 then 0 else decode(dt_du_v, 0, 0, trunc( (d_du_a - dt_du_m) / dt_du_v )) end du_bid, -- service time d_st_a, dt_st_m, dt_st_v, case when dt_st_m > .1 then dt_st_v/dt_st_m else 0 end dt_st_cv, greatest(dt_st_m - 3*dt_st_v, 0) dt_st_l, dt_st_m + 3*dt_st_v dt_st_h, case when (round(dt_st_m, 2) = 0 and round(dt_st_v, 2) = 0 and round(d_st_a, 2) < 1) or round(d_iops_a, 2) < 10 then 0 else decode(dt_st_v, 0, 0, trunc( (d_st_a - dt_st_m) / latency d_sr_a, dt_sr_m, dt_sr_v, case when dt_sr_m > .1 then dt_sr_v/dt_sr_m else 0 end dt_sr_cv, greatest(dt_sr_m - 3*dt_sr_v, 0) dt_sr_l, (dt_sr_m + 3*dt_sr_v) dt_sr_h, case when (round(dt_sr_m, 2) = 0 and round(dt_sr_v, 2) = 0 and round(d_sr_a, 2) < 1) or round(d_srrq_a, 2) < 10 then 0 else decode(dt_sr_v, 0, 0, trunc( (d_sr_a - dt_sr_m) / dt_sr_v )) end sr_bid, -- small write latency d_sw_a, dt_sw_m, dt_sw_v, case when dt_sw_m > .1 then dt_sw_v/dt_sw_m else 0 end dt_sw_cv, greatest(dt_sw_m - 3*dt_sw_v, 0) dt_sw_l, (dt_sw_m + 3*dt_sw_v) dt_sw_h, case when (round(dt_sw_m, 2) = 0 and round(dt_sw_v, 2) = 0 and round(d_sw_a, 2) < 1) or round(d_swrq_a, 2) < 10 then 0 else decode(dt_sw_v, 0, 0, trunc( (d_sw_a - dt_sw_m) / dt_sw_v )) end sw_bid, -- large read latency d_lr_a, dt_lr_m, dt_lr_v, case when dt_lr_m > .1 then dt_lr_v/dt_lr_m else 0 end dt_lr_cv, greatest(dt_lr_m - 3*dt_lr_v, 0) dt_lr_l, (dt_lr_m + 3*dt_lr_v) dt_lr_h, case when (round(dt_lr_m, 2) = 0 and round(dt_lr_v, 2) = 0 and round(d_lr_a, 2) < 1) or round(d_lrrq_a, 2) < 10 then 0 else decode(dt_lr_v, 0, 0, trunc( (d_lr_a - dt_lr_m) / dt_lr_v )) end lr_bid, -- large write latency d_lw_a, dt_lw_m, dt_lw_v, case when dt_lw_m > .1 then dt_lw_v/dt_lw_m else 0 end dt_lw_cv, greatest(dt_lw_m - 3*dt_lw_v, 0) dt_lw_l, (dt_lw_m + 3*dt_lw_v) dt_lw_h, case when (round(dt_lw_m, 2) = 0 and round(dt_lw_v, 2) = 0 and round(d_lw_a, 2) < 1) or round(d_lwrq_a, 2) < 10 then 0 else decode(dt_lw_v, 0, 0, trunc( (d_lw_a - dt_lw_m) / dt_lw_v )) end lw_bid, -- rank iorq_rank, iob_rank iomb_rank, ap_rank from (-- compute per disk type standard deviation select dbid, cell_hash, cell_name, disk_id, disk_name, disk, num_disks, max_iops, max_mbps, -- total IOs d_iorq_a, d_iorq_pct, dt_iorq_m, sqrt( abs(greatest(0, (dt_iorq_sx2 / dt_samples) - (dt_iorq_m*dt_iorq_m) ))) dt_iorq_v, -- small reads d_srrq_a, dt_srrq_m, sqrt( abs(greatest(0, (dt_srrq_sx2 / dt_samples) - (dt_srrq_m*dt_srrq_m) ))) dt_srrq_v, -- small - (dt_lrrq_m*dt_lrrq_m) ))) dt_lrrq_v, -- large writes d_lwrq_a, dt_lwrq_m, sqrt( abs(greatest(0, (dt_lwrq_sx2 / dt_samples) - (dt_lwrq_m*dt_lwrq_m) ))) dt_lwrq_v, -- total bytes d_iob_a/1048576 d_iomb_a, d_iob_pct d_iomb_pct, dt_iob_m/1048576 dt_iomb_m, (sqrt( abs(greatest(0, (dt_iob_sx2 / dt_samples) - (dt_iob_m*dt_iob_m) ))))/ 1048576 dt_iomb_v, -- small read bytes d_srb_a/1048576 d_srmb_a, dt_srb_m/1048576 dt_srmb_m, (sqrt( abs(greatest(0, (dt_srb_sx2 / dt_samples) - (dt_srb_m*dt_srb_m) ))))/ 1048576 dt_srmb_v, -- small write bytes d_swb_a/1048576 d_swmb_a, dt_swb_m/1048576 small read latency d_sr_a/1000 d_sr_a, dt_sr_m/1000 dt_sr_m, (sqrt ( abs(greatest(0, (dt_sr_sx2 / dt_samples) - (dt_sr_m*dt_sr_m) ))))/1000 dt_sr_v, -- small write latency d_sw_a/1000 d_sw_a, dt_sw_m/1000 dt_sw_m, (sqrt ( abs(greatest(0, (dt_sw_sx2 / dt_samples) - (dt_sw_m*dt_sw_m) ))))/1000 dt_sw_v, -- large read latency d_lr_a/1000 d_lr_a, dt_lr_m/1000 dt_lr_m, (sqrt ( abs(greatest(0, (dt_lr_sx2 / dt_samples) - (dt_lr_m*dt_lr_m) ))))/1000 dt_lr_v, -- large write latency d_lw_a/1000 d_lw_a, dt_lw_m/1000 dt_lw_m, (sqrt ( abs(greatest(0, (dt_lw_sx2 / dt_samples) - (dt_lw_m*dt_lw_m) ))))/1000 dt_lw_v, -- rank iorq_rank, iob_rank, ap_rank from (-- get per disk type mean and sum squares select dbid, cell_hash, cell_name, disk_id, disk_name, disk, max_iops, max_mbps, count(distinct over (partition by disk) dt_iorq_m, sum(d_iorq_sx2) over (partition by disk) dt_iorq_sx2, 100*(ratio_to_report(d_iorq_a) over (partition by disk)) d_iorq_pct, -- small reads d_srrq_a, sum(d_srrq_s) dt.cell_hash = s.cell_hash and dt.snap_id = :eid and dt.dbid = ct.dbid and dt.cell_hash = ct.cell_hash and dt.snap_id = ct.snap_id))) ), outlier_stats as ( select dbid, cell_name, disk_id, disk_name, dt_iorq_m > max_iops then 'Y' end is_max_disk_iops, -- small reads d_srrq_a, dt_srrq_m, dt_srrq_v, dt_srrq_cv, dt_srrq_l, dt_srrq_h, srrq_bid, -- small writes d_swrq_a, dt_swrq_m, dt_swrq_v, iorq_rank, iomb_rank, ap_rank from disk_stats ) select /*+ opt_param('_optimizer_skip_scan_enabled', 'false') */ xmlelement("statsgroup", outlier_xml, diskiorq, diskiomb, diskap) from ( select PGA Aggr Target Stats

Top SQL with Top Events

  • Top SQL statements by DB Time along with the top events by DB Time for those SQLs.
  • % Activity is the percentage of DB Time due to the SQL.
  • % Event is the percentage of DB Time due to the event that the SQL is waiting on.
  • % Row Source is the percentage of DB Time due to the row source for the SQL waiting on the event.
  • Executions is the number of executions of the SQL that were sampled in ASH.

  • Blocking session activity percentages are calculated with respect to waits on enqueues, latches and "buffer busy" only
  • '% Activity' represents the load on the database caused by a particular blocking session
  • '# Samples Active' shows the number of ASH samples in which the blocking session was found active.
  • 'XIDs' shows the number of distinct transaction IDs sampled in ASH when the blocking session was found active.

  • Analysis period is divided into smaller time slots as indicated in the 'Slot Time (Duration)'.

  • 'Slot Count' shows the number of ASH samples in that slot
  • 'Event Count' shows the number of ASH samples waiting for that event in that slot
  • '% Event' is 'Event Count' over all ASH samples in the analysis period

Exadata Outlier Summary

  • Exadata Outlier Summary
    • Cell Level
    • Disk Level

Outlier Summary - Cell Level

  • Outliers are cells whose average performance is outside the normal range, where normal range is -/+ 1 standard deviation
  • Outlier cells must have a mininum of 10 IOPs. Idle cells are not considered for outlier analysis.
  • Outliers for hard disks are displayed when Hard Disk IOPs exceeds 76.68 (1% of maximum capacity of 7,668)
  • Outliers for flash disks are displayed when Flash Disk IOPs exceeds 10234.32 (1% of maximum capacity of 1,023,432)
  • Outliers for flash disks will not be displayed. There are only 271 flash IOPs
  • A 'v' and a dark yellow background indicates an outlier value below the low range
  • A '^' and a light red background indicates an outlier value above the high range
  • A '*' and a dark red background indicates over maximum capacity
  • A 'o' and an orange background indicates high standard deviation (high variability in data set)
  • Disk Type <F|H|M>/<size>: F-Flash, H-Hard Disk, M-pMEM; PMEM I/O only include remote I/Os processed by cellsrv
  • Maximum cell capacity for hard disks: IOPS: H/12.5T: 2,556 | IO MB/s: H/12.5T: 1,776
  • Maximum cell capacity for flash disks: IOPS: F/5.8T: 341,144 | IO MB/s: F/5.8T: 25,000
  • There is insufficient activity on Flash Disks, and Flash Disk outliers will not be displayed
  • There are no cell outliers on hard disks

Back to Exadata Outlier Summary
Back to Exadata Resource Statistics

Outlier Summary - Disk Level

  • Outliers are disks whose average performance is outside the normal range, where normal range is -/+ 3 standard deviation
  • Outlier disks must have a mininum of 10 IOPs. Idle disks are not considered for outlier analysis.
  • Outliers for hard disks are displayed when Hard Disk IOPs exceeds 76.68 (1% of maximum capacity of 7,668)
  • Outliers for flash disks are displayed when Flash Disk IOPs exceeds 10234.32 (1% of maximum capacity of 1,023,432)
  • Outliers for flash disks will not be displayed. There are only 271 flash IOPs
  • A 'v' and a dark yellow background indicates an outlier value below the low range
  • A '^' and a light red background indicates an outlier value above the high range
  • A '*' and a dark red background indicates over maximum capacity
  • A 'o' and an orange background indicates high standard deviation (high variability in data set)
  • Disk Type <F|H|M>/<size>: F-Flash, H-Hard Disk, M-pMEM; PMEM I/O only include remote I/Os processed by cellsrv
  • Maximum hard disk capacity: IOPS: H/12.5T: 213 | IO MB/s: H/12.5T: 148
  • Maximum flash disk capacity: IOPS: F/5.8T: 85,286 | IO MB/s: F/5.8T: 6,250
  • There is insufficient activity on Flash Disks, and Flash Disk outliers will not be displayed

Exadata OS IO Statistics - Outlier Cells

  • These statistics are collected by the OS on the cells and are not restricted to this database or instance
  • Outliers are cells whose average performance is outside the normal range, where normal range is -/+ 1 standard deviation
  • Outlier cells must have a mininum of 10 IOPs. Idle cells are not considered for outlier analysis.
  • Outliers for hard disks are displayed when Hard Disk IOPs exceeds 76.68 (1% of maximum capacity of 7,668)
  • Outliers for flash disks are displayed when Flash Disk IOPs exceeds 10234.32 (1% of maximum capacity of 1,023,432)
  • Outliers for flash disks will not be displayed. There are only 271 flash IOPs
  • A 'v' and a dark yellow background indicates an outlier value below the low range
  • A '^' and a light red background indicates an outlier value above the high range
  • A '*' and a dark red background indicates over maximum capacity
  • A 'o' and an orange background indicates high standard deviation (high variability in data set)
  • Disk Type <F|H|M>/<size>: F-Flash, H-Hard Disk, M-pMEM; PMEM I/O only include remote I/Os processed by cellsrv
  • %Total - Avg [IOPs |IO MB/s] of the cell as a percentage of total [IOPs | IO MB/s] for the disk type
  • There are no cell outliers on hard disks

Flash Log Statistics

  • Flash Log
  • Redo Write Histogram

Flash Log

  • These statistics are collected by the cells and are not restricted to this database or instance
  • Write Requests Flash Log - writes serviced by flash log
  • Write Requests Redo Log - redo writes serviced including those that bypass flash log
    Database redo log writes are typically written to both flash log and redo log
  • FC Writes - redo writes absorbed by flash cache that would have otherwise gone to database redo logs on disk
  • FC Skips - redo writes bypassing flash cache
  • Write MB - write bytes serviced by flash log
  • First Writes Flash Log - writes written first to smart flash log
  • First Writes DB Log - writes written first to database redo log file
  • % Efficiency - percentage when flash log prevented writes from exceeding the threshold
  • Prevented - flash log writes prevented from exceeding outlier threshold
  • Actual - flash log writes that exceeded outlier threshold
  • Disk I/O Errors - disk I/O errors encountered by flash log (should be 0)
  • Flash I/O Errors - flash I/O errors encountered by flash log (should be 0)
  • Keep - redo saved on flash due to disk I/O errors (should be 0)
  • Skip Count - redo writes not serviced by flash log (should be 0)
  • Ordered by Total Write Requests desc
Write Requests Write MB First Writes Outliers Errors

PMEM Log Bypass Reasons

  • These statistics are collected by the cells and are not restricted to this database or instance
  • Bypass - redo writes that bypass PMEM log
  • The following possible reasons for bypassing PMEM log are displayed:
    • Unknown - bypass due to: unknown
    • No valid bands - bypass due to: no valid bands
    • RDMA connection - bypass due to: no band info
    • Data size - bypass due to: data size exceeds largest configured band
    • RDMA disabled - bypass due to: IPCDAT temporarily disabled due to recent error
    • RDMA capability - bypass due to: no IPCDAT capability
    • Cell connection - bypass due to: deferred connect in progress
    • Memory registrations - bypass due to: max memory registrations
    • Memory failures - bypass due to: memory allocation failure
    • RDMA key - bypass due to: kgipc get-key failure
    • Ineligible buffer - bypass due to: ineligible data buffer
    • RDMA error - bypass due to: IPCDAT error
    • Reason614 - bypass due to: encrypted connection
    • Reason615 - bypass due to: ineligible request

Flash Cache User Writes - Large Write Rejections

  • These statistics are collected by the cells and are not restricted to this database or instance
  • Eligible - does not include Global Criteria rejections
  • Large writes may be rejected for the following reasons:
  • Disk Not Busy - IORM determined the hard disk is not busy
  • Misc - large write rejections after passing global criteria
  • CG Thrashing - large writes are causing flash cache group thrashing
  • LW Thrashing - large writes are causing thrashing
  • Max Limit - flash cache size for large writes is at flash cache group limit
  • Global Limit - flash cache size for large writes is over global limit
  • Flash Wear - large writes are causing excessive flash wear
  • Flash Busy - flash is busy
  • Keep - keep needs the cache lines
